notes: Conditional logic via Python control flow

components.name: Analyze Transactions
components.description: Reads daily transaction CSV files and calculates a fraud risk score for each batch.

components.name: Route Transaction
components.description: Evaluates the risk score and decides whether to route the transaction to manual review or autoapproval based on a threshold.

components.name: Process Manual Review
components.description: Sends highrisk transactions to a manual review queue for analyst assessment.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered only when route_transaction selects the manual review branch

connections.purpose: Enqueue highrisk transactions for manual analyst review

components.name: Process Auto Approval
components.description: Sends lowrisk transactions to the payment processing system for automatic approval.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered only when route_transaction selects the autoapproval branch

connections.purpose: Submit lowrisk transactions for automatic payment processing

components.name: Send Notification
components.description: Sends a final notification to the fraud detection team after both manual review and autoapproval paths have completed.

upstream_policy.description: Executes after both manual review and autoapproval tasks complete without failure

connections.purpose: Notify fraud detection team of pipeline completion

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

sources: Daily transaction CSV files stored on the local filesystem at /data/transactions/daily
sinks: Email notification sent to the fraud detection team via the SMTP notification service
